		"description": "<p>Skilled eldritch archers can subvert their arcane power to enchant the conjured arrows with rings of eldritch symbols and energy that form around their weapons as they fire.&nbsp;</p><p>Whenever you make a ranged weapon attack, you may choose to expend a 1st-level spell slot or higher to enhance the attack to be empowered or unerring. You cannot enhance more than one attack in a turn in this way.</p><p><strong><em>Empowered.</em> </strong>An empowered shot deals an additional 2d6 force damage, and an additional 1d6 force damage for each spell slot level above 1st.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><em>Unerring.</em></strong> An unerring shot gains a +2 bonus to the attack roll, and an additional +2 bonus for each spell slot level above 1st.</p>",
